  {
    "client_msg_id": "9232acff-0d90-4386-822e-871d21ca123c",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I know y'all are mostly kidding, but it's such a prevalent voice in my own head that I want to explicitly say:\n• it's impossible, and\n• it's not desirable even if it was possible.\nThe instinct comes from a sense that we know what's best and we're just ordering the computer around. But we seldom know what's best when we start writing a program. We don't understand the consequences of our desires.\n\nElsewhere people have said that writing is for generating ideas, not just communicating them. Programming is for understanding our own desires, not just translating them.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1639932447.289100",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
